Government and health authorities have claimed the cholera situation in Chegutu is now under control and that the disease has been contained. But conversations with residents of the town reveal a different story. The residents speak of a town that has malfunctioning sewer and water systems that remain the biggest factor in the recurrence of Cholera. <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/koDInPBzRrk" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>